            <h1><br>Are there crops in the photo?</h1>
			<p>
            <a target="_blank" id="uri" class="btn" href="http://blog.cafod.org.uk/tag/climate-change/"><i class="fa fa-white fa-search"></i>View context of this photo</a>
            </p>
			<div class="row help_popup col-xs-12">
			<i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i> How do I answer this question? <a class="help_popup_a" href="javascript:void(0)">Get some help</a>
				<div class="help_popup_description col-xs-12">
					<p>This is a simple filtering question to remove any photos that do not have crops in them and therefore are not relevant to the analysis.</p>
					<p>Click "yes" if you see crop plants in the photo</p>
					<p>If you are not sure what you are looking at, look for some of the following signs:</p>
					<ul><li>Machinery, tools, irrigation, and other items associated with agriculture</li>
						<li>Plants are in rows</li>
						<li>Fences, hedgerows or other marking the boundaries of a field</li>
						<li>Homogeneity in the field - all the plants are the same species, the same height, and/or look the same age</li></ul>
					<p>You should also click "yes" if the crop appears dead as these can still give lots of information about the environmental conditions in the area</p>
						
