        <div id="step_3" class="steps col-xs-6">
           <h1>Are the crops green?</h1>
			<div class="row help_popup col-xs-12">
				<i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i>How do I answer this question? <a class="help_popup_a" href="javascript:void(0)">Get some help</a>
				<div class="help_popup_description col-xs-12">
					<p>This gives an indication of if the crops are alive or not. Crops that are not green may have suffered from water stress (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_scarcity">What is water stress</a>). If the crops are not green it does not necessarily mean that they are suffering from water stress. Some crops might look dry and dead but in fact they are senescing or drying down at the end of their life-cycle, just before being harvested. This is a normal part of the production cycle for crops such as corn. In this question, however, we just need to know if the crops are green or not.</p>
					<p><strong>Click Yes</strong> if you can see green in the plant</p>
					<p><strong>Click No</strong> if the plants have no green at all, or less than 10% green</p>
					<hr>
					<p>Below are some examples for which you should click "yes"</p>
					<div class="row">
						<div class="col-sm-6">
							<p>Green healthy crops (this is a millet field)</p>
							<a target="_blank" href="http://static.panoramio.com/photos/large/45493424.jpg"><img style="width:400px;" src="http://static.panoramio.com/photos/large/45493424.jpg" class="img-thumbnail"></a>
							<p style="font-size:10px;"><span class="fa fa-picture"></i> <a href="http://www.panoramio.com/user/4324714?with_photo_id=45493424">Cory Enger</a></p>
							
						</div>
						<div class="col-sm-6">
							<p>Crops that appear partially dry</p>
							<a target="_blank" href="http://www.standeyo.com/NEWS/08_Food_Water/08_Food_Water_pics/080121.corn.drought.jpg"><img style="width:400px;" src="http://www.standeyo.com/NEWS/08_Food_Water/08_Food_Water_pics/080121.corn.drought.jpg" class="img-thumbnail"></a>
